description:
As a naturopathic doctor, Dr. Rob McClintock brings his medical expertise and research to the subject of cardiovascular disease, which has much in common with diabetes. He explains statistics related to who gets it, how people cope with it, how many live and die, and how devastating and how survivable it is. Watch this lecture to learn how heart disease is not genetic, the various steps you can take to prevent it and actions you can take to reverse it if you do have it.

Visit our website: http://amazingdiscoveries.org

http://amazingdiscoveries.tv/c/193/Discover_Total_Health/
